reviews.review:
parking lot at 5th and Howard Street has been a major public nuisance.

For example:

·      ugly, rusty cyclone fence always in the need of repair,

Any property improvement that did occur resulted because neighbors complained to the proper authorities, such as Public Works or the Community Benefits District about the shotty condition of the parking lot.

The people running the parking lot (and the property owners) never lifted a finger to improve the condition of that lot on their own.

reviews.name: C B.
reviews.review:
I would leave a negative review if I could. I stayed at the Parc 55 and had my car parked by valet. Upon returning my car, I had a ding in the passenger side door. I reported this immediately to an attendant. I later received a letter from Connecticut stating the ding was pre- existing (which is a highly incorrect statement). I asked for evidence to support this claim. The representative from Propark then emailed me a piece of paper from Propark with a car diagram on it with an X on the passenger side door. The representative stated this was the proof that the ding was pre- existing. Unbelievable! This was not a diagram filled out after a joint inspection by the attendant and myself in which I signed in agreement. This was offered after the fact. When I made the initial complaint at Parc 55, the supervisor took a report and did not even mention this "evidence". This evidence was created after the report was taken I am sure. Before I leave my car with any valet service, I walk around it in order to check the body. I take very good care of my car. Due to the valet service,
My family and I will never stay at this location again. Where is the honorable and just business practice? This whole experience was highly unsavory and dishonest.

reviews.name: David M.
reviews.review:
Horrible experience. After paying at the pay station and immediately walking to my car, we drove down from the fourth floor to the exit on the first. Due to traffic congestion inside the garage, we exceeded the time permitted. 

Once denied exit, I used the intercom to ask for assistance. I was only given short responses which were difficult to understand due to the poor audio quality but were instructing me to leave my car to walk to the pay station. After several requests for clarification, they stopped answering my calls via the intercom entirely.  Eventually, an employee tasked with traffic management refused to help with exiting, but he did direct traffic to let me back up so I could park on the bottom floor and make the payment. After parking on the first floor, and heading toward the pay station, one employee did listen to my complaint and offered to let me out through a different exit.

Two of the three employees I had to deal with were extremely unprofessional and frankly quite rude. The entire experience was extremely frustrating.

reviews.name: Chris D.
reviews.review: The garage itself is fine but the staff are extremely unprofessional. Any minor "infringement" of their draconian monthly parking agreement and they immediately hit you a lost ticket charges. This includes forgetting your tag, any minor billing issues, etc. Steer clear of this place. They even disabled my card in the middle of the day once and wouldn't let me escape the place until I coughed up $34 (despite having paid $315/month for over a year with no other issues).
